api_analysis_prompt.user_prompt_template:
Analyze the following API documentation and extract comprehensive details for creating a production-ready MCP tool.

API DOCUMENTATION:
{api_documentation}

Determine if this is a REST API or Python Package API, then provide a detailed JSON response with the appropriate structure:

For REST APIs, use this structure:
{{
    "api_type": "rest",
    "api_name": "Clear, descriptive name for the API",
    "description": "Comprehensive description of API functionality and use cases",
    "base_url": "Complete base URL including protocol",
    "endpoints": [
        {{
            "path": "/specific/endpoint/path",
            "method": "GET|POST|PUT|DELETE|PATCH",
            "description": "Detailed description of endpoint functionality",
            "summary": "Brief one-line summary for tool descriptions"
        }}
    ],
    "parameters": {{
        "param_name": {{
            "type": "string|integer|boolean|number|array|object",
            "description": "Detailed parameter description with constraints",
            "required": true|false,
            "default": "default_value_or_null",
            "enum": ["option1", "option2"] || null,
            "pattern": "regex_pattern_if_applicable" || null,
            "minimum": 0 || null,
            "maximum": 100 || null,
            "example": "example_value"
        }}
    }},
    "authentication": {{
        "type": "api_key|bearer_token|basic_auth|oauth2|none",
        "location": "header|query|body",
        "parameter_name": "exact_parameter_or_header_name",
        "scheme": "Bearer|Basic|ApiKey" || null,
        "description": "How to obtain and use authentication"
    }},
    "response_format": {{
        "type": "json|xml|text|binary",
        "content_type": "application/json|text/xml|text/plain",
        "structure": "Detailed description of response structure and key fields",
        "example": {{
            "sample_field": "sample_value"
        }}
    }}
}}

For Python Package APIs, use this structure:
{{
    "api_type": "python_package",
    "api_name": "Clear, descriptive name for the package",
    "description": "Comprehensive description of package functionality and use cases",
    "package_name": "exact_package_name_for_import",
    "main_function": {{
        "name": "primary_function_name",
        "import_statement": "from package import function, Class1, Class2",
        "description": "What the main function does"
    }},
    "parameters": {{
        "param_name": {{
            "type": "string|integer|boolean|number|array|object|custom_class",
            "description": "Detailed parameter description with constraints",
            "required": true|false,
            "default": "default_value_or_null",
            "enum": ["option1", "option2"] || null,
            "class_structure": {{
                "field1": "type_and_description",
                "field2": "type_and_description"
            }} || null,
            "example": "example_value_or_object"
        }}
    }},
    "authentication": {{
        "type": "none|api_key|file_based|environment",
        "description": "Authentication requirements if any"
    }},
    "response_format": {{
        "type": "object|dataclass|dict|list",
        "class_name": "ResponseClassName" || null,
        "structure": {{
            "main_attribute": {{
                "type": "list|object|string",
                "description": "What this contains",
                "item_structure": {{
                    "field1": "type_and_description",
                    "field2": "type_and_description"
                }} || null
            }}
        }},
        "example": {{
            "attribute1": "sample_value",
            "attribute2": [
                {{
                    "field1": "sample",
                    "field2": "sample"
                }}
            ]
        }}
    }},
    "installation": {{
        "command": "pip install package-name",
        "requirements": ["dependency1", "dependency2"]
    }}
}}

Common fields for both types:
{{
    "error_handling": {{
        "common_errors": [
            {{
                "type": "ValueError|ConnectionError|AuthError|etc",
                "description": "When this error occurs"
            }}
        ]
    }},
    "usage_examples": [
        {{
            "description": "Example use case description",
            "parameters": {{
                "param1": "example_value1",
                "param2": "example_value2"
            }},
            "expected_response": "Brief description of expected response"
        }}
    ],
    "tool_metadata": {{
        "category": "weather|news|finance|social|utility|data|ai|travel|other",
        "tags": ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3"],
        "complexity": "simple|moderate|complex",
        "requires_auth": true|false,
        "rate_limited": true|false
    }}
}}

IMPORTANT GUIDELINES:
- Carefully determine if this is a REST API or Python package
- For Python packages, focus on the main function and its parameters
- Extract ALL available parameters, even optional ones
- For custom classes/objects, describe their structure
- Include comprehensive error handling information
- Provide realistic usage examples
- If information is missing, use reasonable defaults based on API type
- For Python packages, the response structure should match the actual return objects

Respond with ONLY the JSON, no additional text or formatting.
